If you happen to be in Jackson Heights spot by  to have a good drink and a good meal come here you won't be disappointed. Especially happy hour 3-7 Monday-friday. Great staff, fast service and always treated like family. Can't wait to be back again

Been here 3 times, the staff is very friendly. Family owned restaurant in jackson heights, the drinks are phenomenal and happy hours slamming. If you are looking for a nice and quite spot with amazing food and drink, get off at 74 walk to 77th and make a right and you won't be disappointed.

The French Toast and coffee was really good.

Our waitress was very rude. She got our order wrong twice and was becoming very annoyed towards us especially since we talked to her very nicely during this whole ordeal. She would rather stand there and argue with us than fix the order and argued with us saying we ordered something else. I am not sure how it is a coincidence that she got 2 of our orders wrong. Towards the end, she stopped coming to our table and sent another employee to assist us. She also stood by the bar and stared at our table while talking with another co-worker. Not sure what they were saying but it seemed odd they were talking and staring at out direction. Food was good but Bad service.

Came here on a summer night and had tacos here. Awesome food and even better personnel. Great customer service and amazing food. Good vibe on roosy and good food? What else can you ask for?
Awesome spot in Jackson Heights. Delicious food, big portions, and super friendly staff. Highly recommended!

Great brunch options, some unique to the hood. Carribean French toast is a must, with a side of bacon!

I honestly don't know how this place has such great reviews, I was excited for brunch, but this place is not worth it. The prices are definitely elevated, the french toast with berries, literally included two slices of bread and  half of a slice of strawberry.  The one entree and one free beverage was not upheld. I asked for my steak medium rare, it was well done. I asked for my eggs scrambled, they gave them to me sunnyside up. I love supporting small businesses, especially during this time, but the food should at least be decent and the server shouldn't be so rude and know basic questions about the menu. I wish I would have taken pictures so people would see how the food really looks. I advise you to check your bill because I got charged for things i didn't order.

The food was good, went there for brunch on a sunday. We ate inside the restaurant becuz it was too cold that sunday. We had plenty of space between tables. I had the poet's eggs Benedict with salad and potatoes and a glass of sangria.‚Ä¶
